<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="SQ3" checkit-title="Partial sum sequence">
    <statement>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Consider the partial sum sequence <m>\displaystyle A_n=\left(1\right)+\left(-\frac{2}{3}\right)+\left(\frac{4}{9}\right)+\cdots+\left(1\cdot \left( -\frac{2}{3}\right)^n \right).</m>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Find a closed form for <m>A_n</m>.</li>
                        <li>Does <m>\{A_n\}</m> converge?  If so, to what value?</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                    Consider the partial sum sequence <m>\displaystyle B_n=\sum_{i=1}^n \left( \frac{1}{4 \, i + 3}-\frac{1}{4 \, i + 7} \right).</m>
                    <ol>
                        <li>Find a closed form for <m>B_n</m>.</li>
                        <li>Does <m>\{B_n\}</m> converge?  If so, to what value?</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                
            </ol>
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <ol>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle A_n=1\cdot\frac{1-\left(-\frac{2}{3}\right)^{n+1} }{1- \left(-\frac{2}{3}\right) }</m>.</li>
                        <li>
                            <m>\displaystyle\lim_{n\to\infty} 1\cdot\frac{1-\left(-\frac{2}{3}\right)^{n+1} }{1- \left(-\frac{2}{3}\right) } </m> converges to <m>\frac{3}{5}</m>.                
                        </li>            
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <ol>
                        <li><m>\displaystyle B_n=\frac{1}{7}-\frac{1}{4 \, n + 7}</m>.</li>
                        <li>
                            <m>\displaystyle\lim_{n\to\infty} \frac{1}{7}-\frac{1}{4 \, n + 7} </m> converges to <m>\frac{1}{7}</m>.                
                        </li>            
                    </ol>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
